dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Britain's wait for a first gold of these Games will have to wait for another day after he was agonisingly pipped to the Olympic title in the 100metre breaststroke by just two-hundredths of a second  This was supposed to be the talisman of the Britishswimmingteam's crowning glory to become the only man aside from Michael Phelps to win a hat-trick of Olympic titles in an individual event.\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.99978555579206, \"rank\": 0.00021418654814291894, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 649, \"end\": 663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.720147868353651e-51, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inside La Defense Arena, that defence was instead denied by the slightest of touches by the unheralded Nicolo Martinenghi.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"score\": 0.9999999871765796, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolo Martinenghi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the aftermath of the defeat, he talked about having already won just to have made it to Paris after years of turmoil, mental-health battles and a reliance on alcohol.\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 941, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.412163138217721e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were tears but he insisted not of defeat.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were, he said, \\\"because it took so much to get here\\\".\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty had been lost to swimming and had to be coaxed back into the pool by his coach Mel Marshall, with whom he has an occasionally combative relationship.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He claimed in Paris he had recaptured his love for the sport and suggested in the heats and the semi-finals that he was the man to beat.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1300, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.412163138217721e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But watched by his girlfriend Holly, daughter of the celebrity chef Gordon Ramsay, and son George, holding a Union flag between them, the three-Peaty as it were wasn't to be.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9461874348314713e-40, \"text\": \"Gordon Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His time of 59.05 was way down on his better times but that is partly down to the vagaries of a Parisian pool created solely for these Games.\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In my heart I have won, these are happy tears.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I gave my absolute best every single day and I cannot be upset about that  Adam Peaty  Holly Ramsay posts father Gordon Ramsay's reaction to her on wedding day  Adam Peaty's family 'give up hope of reconciliation after Ramsay's wedding comment'  Gordon Ramsay on how he kept Holly 'calm' at Adam Peaty wedding amid family feud  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  He had a weak start but found himself neck and neck for the lead with China's Qin Haiyang, who had arrived in Paris in a cloud of controversy as one of a group of swimmers who had tested positive for a banned substance but were cleared on contamination grounds.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 2420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9461874348314713e-40, \"text\": \"Gordon Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramsay_Bolton\", \"score\": 